I would be interested in knowing exactly what kind of technical reason was causing the BSODs and systems reboot. I have heard that MrxCls.sys was starting its execution too early immediately after the system boot and went in conflict with other system-related DLLs and high-priority device drivers (namely HAL.DLL). Am I correct? Can you please give some technical details? Is it true that Duqu has corrected this mistake?<br />
Thank you!<br />
Mike</p>
					
