	            <div class="txt">
					
					<h4>Michael OKane</h4>
	        		
	        		<p>An interesting consequence of Stuxnet in Iran was the attack on Saudi Aramco. More than 25,000 hard drives had to be trashed, including the company&#8217;s back-ups. Employees who made (unauthorized) copies of their own workstations were the company&#8217;s salvation, otherwise work would have stopped for much longer than it did. Of course, officially no attack ever took place and the back-ups came on line immediately.</p>
					
